Professor Ninian Peckitt is accused of repeatedly punching a patient in the face to correct a fracture caused by an industrial accident . 
  He claimed he had 'digitally manipulated' the patient but witnesses said he was hitting him . 
  The 63-year-old faces being struck off the medical register . 
  He was working as an honorary locum at Ipswich Hospital . 
  Medical tribunal will decide whether he should be struck off . 
 